article.description: Brittany Rayburn had 25 points and point guard Brandie Baker scored all 16 of hers in the second half and Central Michigan upset Purdue 75-62 on Sunday.
article.headline: No. 14 Purdue loses in road test at Central Michigan
article.linkText: No. 14 Purdue loses in road test at C. Michigan
article.story:
MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. --  Brittany Rayburn had 25 points and point guard Brandie Baker scored all 16 of hers in the second half and Central Michigan upset Purdue (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP)  75-62 on Sunday.

The Chippewas (3-5) outscored the Boilermakers (7-3) 47-25 in the second half as they shot 14 for 24 from the field, including 6 of 9 from 3-point range.

Purdue, which was coming off a loss to No. 3 Notre Dame on Saturday, led 37-28 at halftime.

Freshmen Crystal Bradford and Jessica Green both scored 14 points for Central Michigan.

KK Houser added 11 points and Sam Osatarello had for Purdue, which shot 40 percent from the field (25 for 62), including 3 of 14 from beyond the arc.
